-- GE falls before stock offering
-- 
-- Thu Oct 2, 2008 9:31am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/02/us-markets-stocks-ge-idUSTRE4914OK20081002

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - General Electric ( GE.N ) shares fell 8.7 percent to $22.38 before the bell on Thursday before of an expected stock offering. 

 The diversified manufacturer announced a day ago that it plans to raise $15 billion through stock sales, with $3 billion coming from Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway ( BRKa.N ).